      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "To help you subvert tropes, it's useful to know what they are; some common examples include the \"Orientalist\" trope for East Asians suggesting treachery or meekness, and the \"Angry Black Woman\" or exaggerated \"Jungle Jim\" stereotypes for Black characters. For Hispanic characters, stereotypes often involve portraying them as either perpetually comedic or fiercely passionate. Similarly, tropes surrounding white characters can range from the oblivious \"straight man\" to the exaggeratedly fearful or overly privileged.",
