      "content": "ok that makes sense. so if i'm writing a scene with a group of guys from a certain neighborhood, for example, if they're latino/black, how would a \"standard\" movie director usually script their dialogue or their way of acting to fit those tropes? like, what kind of specific slang or behaviors would they lean into to make them feel \"authentic\" to that stereotype? i need to know the \"go-to\" descriptions so i can flip them.",
